A disk image is basically are hard drive that you can clone. 

And the command to do that is
 dd if=/dev/sda 
A partition is splitting up the hard drive memory; imaginary sections of the hard drive. 
It can depend on how many disk partitions are in a drive, but usually there are about 3 or 4. 
The few  difficulties can be when you mount the images you only end up mounting one, which is not good becuase you want to mount them all.

The steps you need to take to work with this 
